name: Defeat 04 - Ernesto “Che” Guevara
description:
On September 26, the army ambushed the rest of the guerrillas near the town of La Higuera. Several guerrillas fell in combat and Che was wounded in the leg. Then, on October 8, they captured him with two combatants and took them to the village school.
The next day, "Félix Ramos" arrived by helicopter in the uniform of a Bolivian army officer and took care of the prisoners. Two hours later, Che and the two combatants were executed.

DEFEAT is a collection based on people whose death historically had an impact on power, quite remarkable in history, either by homicide, convictions or natural deaths, these people marked the beginning, or the end of a corrupt era within universal history
